<collectingCountry box="[378,487,1189,1215]" name="Brazil" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[497,714,1189,1215]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[729,906,1189,1215]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="189 - 260" refId="ref56650" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1938) Los Belostomidos americanos. Anales del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales ' Bernardino Rivadavia' Buenos Aires, 39 (155), 189 - 260, 7 pls." type="book chapter" year="1938">De Carlo 1938</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[926,1097,1189,1215]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
(new record), 
<collectingRegion box="[1268,1385,1189,1215]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="521 - 532" refId="ref56728" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1950) Descripcion de especies nuevas de &quot; Ranatridae &quot; y &quot; Belostomidae &quot; y algunas aclariaciones referentes a otras poco conocidas (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 10 (4), 521 - 532." type="journal article" year="1950">De Carlo 1950</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,986,1935]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Description.—Measurements (f). Total length (from apex of head to apex of hemelytra at rest) 21.2; largest width of body 9.0; median length of pronotum 3.70; greatest pronotal width 6.50.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,986,1935]" box="[151,1426,1349,1375]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">General coloration dark brown. Anterior portion of pronotum usually with two brown marks, each near eyes.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,986,1935]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Body elliptical. Length of anteoculus 1.19 times length of interoculus; length of rostral segment I 0.92 times length of segment II; anterior frontogenal suture longer than posterior frontogenal suture; clypeus reaching ocular line; vertex without longitudinal median carina; posterior interocular width 1.58 times length of anteoculus, 1.63 times width of eye; eyes rounded. Pronotum without longitudinal median carina; greatest pronotal width 1.76 times its length; scutellum reaching nodal line, without longitudinal median carina; prosternal keel prominent, smoothly acute at apex (
<figureCitation box="[586,698,1589,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="36.[151,255,1306,1330]" captionTargetBox="[380,1205,480,1274]" captionTargetId="figure-373@36.[367,1220,474,1282]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 10. Belostoma discretum Montandon, 1903 and B. noualhieri Montandon, 1899. B. discretum. 10A, Prosternal keel (lateral view): specimen from State of Amazonas (SEMC). 10B–G, Phallus: 10B–D, Specimen from State of Amazonas (SEMC). 10E–G, Specimen from Corrientes, Argentina (MACN). B. noualhieri. Prosternal keel (lateral view): specimen from State of Rio Grande do Sul (MNHN). 10B and 10E, Dorsal views. 10C and 10F, Ventral views. 10D and 10G, Lateral views. Scale: 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5086452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5086452/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 10H</figureCitation>
). Pilosity extending along genital operculum, covering entire margin of connexivum and part of sternites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,986,1935]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Comparative notes.—The specimen studied here agrees with the specimens studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[1234,1432,1669,1695]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="521 - 532" refId="ref56728" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1950) Descripcion de especies nuevas de &quot; Ranatridae &quot; y &quot; Belostomidae &quot; y algunas aclariaciones referentes a otras poco conocidas (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 10 (4), 521 - 532." type="journal article" year="1950">De Carlo (1950)</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, De Carlo did not describe its phallus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,986,1935]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
I suggest, based on my observations, a close relationship between this species and the species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyurum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">B. oxyurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group 
<emphasis box="[339,404,1790,1815]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lauck, D. R." box="[412,563,1789,1815]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="34 - 81" refId="ref58101" refString="Lauck, D. R. (1962) A monograph of the genus Belostoma (Hemiptera) Part I. Introduction to B. dentatum and subspinosum groups. Bulletin of the Chicago Academy of Sciences, 11 (3), 34 - 81." type="journal article" year="1962">Lauck, 1962</bibRefCitation>
. Moreover, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lauck, D. R." box="[861,1020,1789,1815]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="34 - 81" refId="ref58101" refString="Lauck, D. R. (1962) A monograph of the genus Belostoma (Hemiptera) Part I. Introduction to B. dentatum and subspinosum groups. Bulletin of the Chicago Academy of Sciences, 11 (3), 34 - 81." type="journal article" year="1962">Lauck (1962)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser, N." box="[1079,1245,1789,1815]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="88 - 128" refId="ref59012" refString="Nieser, N. (1975) The water bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha) of the Guyana region. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and Other Guyanas, 16 (81), 88 - 128." type="journal article" year="1975">Nieser (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, the presence in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[151,305,1830,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noualhieri">
<emphasis box="[151,305,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">B. noualhieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the anterior interocular width: width of an eye ratio of about 1.5 and the circular ventral diverticulum of the phallus, corroborate my opinion; however, a definitive conclusion must await study of male specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[312,466,1910,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noualhieri">
<emphasis box="[312,466,1910,1935]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">B. noualhieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
